> [!NOTE]
> Full-stack testing (login, project creation, file upload) requires PostgreSQL running. Start with `docker-compose up postgres`, copy [.env.example](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/.env.example) to [.env](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/.env), then run `npm run dev` from the root.

---

## Getting Started

```bash
# 1. Copy environment variables
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your PostgreSQL credentials, JWT secret, etc.

# 2. Start PostgreSQL
docker compose up -d postgres

# 3. Install dependencies
npm install

# 4. Run both client and server
npm run dev
```

The app will be available at `http://localhost:5175` with the API at `http://localhost:3001`.
